@redwolfe98 Hi. It seems caused by `Dandelion Sprout's Annoyances List`.
Please test in user rules:
`ghacks.net#@##comments`

I can reproduce. These rules seem working for me

```adblock
x.com#$#div[role="group"] > div[style]:not([class]):has(> div[class] > div[class] > a[href^="https://apps.apple.com/app/apple-store/"]) { display: none !important; }
x.com#$#div[role="group"] > div[data-testid="mask"] { display: none !important; }
x.com#$#html[style] { overflow: auto !important; position: static !important; }
```

It is blocked by AdGuard Other Annoyances

```adblock
wikipedia.org#$#.frb-overlay-open { overflow: auto !important; }
wikipedia.org#$#.cn-fundraising { display: none !important; }
```

This works for me, but not so happy with the solution:
```
bhaskar.com#%#setTimeout(function(){var el_array = window.INITIAL_STATE.homeData.homePageFeedV2.feed; el_array.forEach(function(el_array){ var el = document.querySelector("a[href*=" + CSS.escape(el_array.id) + "]"); el.setAttribute("href",el_array.data.shortUrl); el.setAttribute("target",'_blank'); if(el_array.data.webStoryAction) {el_array.data.webStoryAction.androidUrl = el_array.data.shortUrl; el_array.data.webStoryAction.iosUrl = el_array.data.shortUrl; el_array.data.webStoryAction.webUrl = el_array.data.shortUrl;} });}, 500);
bhaskar.com#%#//scriptlet("prevent-addEventListener", "click", "div#root")
```

